ds this would be relatively easy to do in theory.  Say, Sol Ro wizards get like a 2% benefit to land a fire-based spell and 1/2 of 1% chance to crit with fire spells.  Prexus could be on the Ice-based, Innoruuk could be magic, etc, etc.  <br>
<br>
Such bonuses would be nice, but wouldn't be so much that specific wizards would be given choice over others, and at the same time perhaps give each class something more than a Ken vs. Ryu scenario. <p><b>Orakkus Mu'hadeeb</b><br>
<i>Evoker of the 56th Circle of Burning Hellice</i><br>Adventuring for the Triad of Honor.<br><br>

Wizards may not be welcomed in groups.. but we are always welcomed at parties.  Why?  Because we do them all.. and we do them good.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1781<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/12/02 6:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Diety Improved DDs</span><hr size=1> Great idea. I too had thought about this, but since spells (at the time) couldn't be diety restricted, I decided not to post it.<br>
<br>
Since the last patch they can now code spells by religion, so it would make a great deal of sense to make cultural or religious spells. It would further differenciate between classes of different races, and also give those that chose a religion even more of an advantage.<br>
<br>
Personally, I'd make the spells quested or researched from the dieties temple. Also, there should be upgrades available, so players can continue to use these spells throughout their levels.<br>
<br>
